ocytosis or cytolysis mechanisms via complement or Fc receptors following the binding of antibodies to cell surface antigens on a target cell.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12640:def: \"An inflammatory response resulting in cell death or dysfunction mediated by the direct binding of antibody to cellular receptors.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12649:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of type IIa hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12657:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of type IIa hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12669:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type IIa hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12682:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of type IIb hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12690:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of type IIb hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12702:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type IIb hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12715:def: \"An inflammatory response resulting from recognition of immune complexes via complement or Fc receptors on effector cells leading to activation of neutrophils and other leukocytes and damage to bystander tissue.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12726:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of type III hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12734:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of type III hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12746:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type III hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12760:def: \"An inflammatory response driven by T cell recognition of processed soluble or cell-associated antigens leading to cytokine release and leukocyte activation.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12771:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of type IV hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12779:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of type IV hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12791:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type IV hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12804:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of type I hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12812:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of type I hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:12824:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type I hypersensitivity, a type of inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17211:name: leukocyte chemotaxis involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17213:def: \"The movement of an immune cell in response to an external stimulus contributing to an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17214:synonym: \"immune cell chemotaxis during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17215:synonym: \"leucocyte chemotaxis during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17216:synonym: \"leukocyte chemotaxis during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17218:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17331:name: wound healing involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17333:def: \"The series of events that restore integrity to damaged tissue that contribute to an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal, ISBN:0721601871]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17334:synonym: \"healing during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17335:synonym: \"inflammatory response wound healing\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17338:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17339:relationship: part_of GO:0090594 ! inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17343:name: obsolete clearance of damaged tissue involved in inflammatory response wound healing\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17345:def: \"OBSOLETE. The series of events leading to removal of necrotic debris that contribute to an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal, ISBN:0721601871]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17347:synonym: \"clearance of damaged tissue during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17353:name: connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17355:def: \"The series of events leading to growth of connective tissue when loss of tissues that are incapable of regeneration occurs, or when fibrinous exudate cannot be adequately cleared, as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal, PMID:9639571]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17356:synonym: \"connective tissue replacement during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17357:synonym: \"fibrosis during inflammatory response\" NARROW [ISBN:0721601871]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17360:relationship: part_of GO:0002246 ! wound healing involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17410:is_a: GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17551:name: leukocyte activation involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17553:def: \"A change in the morphology or behavior of a leukocyte resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17554:synonym: \"immune cell activation during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17555:synonym: \"leukocyte activation during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:tb]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:17558:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18526:name: histamine production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18528:def: \"The synthesis or release of histamine following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149, PMID:16730260]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18529:synonym: \"histamine production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18530:is_a: GO:0002532 ! production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18545:name: serotonin production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18547:def: \"The synthesis or release of serotonin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149, PMID:16730260]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18548:synonym: \"serotonin production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18549:is_a: GO:0002532 ! production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18934:name: obsolete platelet activating factor production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18939:def: \"OBSOLETE. The synthesis or release of platelet activating factor following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18942:synonym: \"platelet activating factor production involved in acute inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18944:synonym: \"platelet activating factor secretion involved in acute inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18945:synonym: \"platelet activating factor secretion involved in inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18954:name: obsolete lysosomal enzyme production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18956:def: \"OBSOLETE. The synthesis or release of lysosomal enzymes following a stimulus as part of a inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18958:synonym: \"lysosomal enzyme production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18959:synonym: \"production of lysosomal enzymes involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:18960:synonym: \"production of lysosomal enzymes involved in inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19327:def: \"The formation of nodular inflammatory lesions, usually small or granular, firm, persistent, well-structured, and containing compactly grouped T lymphocytes and modified phagocytes such as epithelioid cells, giant cells, and other macrophages. Granuloma formation represents a chronic inflammatory response initiated by various infectious and noninfectious agents. The center of a granuloma consists of fused macrophages, which can become necrotic.\" [GO_REF:0000022, GOC:add, ISBN:068340007X, ISBN:0721601464, ISBN:081533642X]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19329:relationship: part_of GO:0002544 ! chronic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19369:name: inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19371:def: \"An inflammatory response to an antigenic stimulus, which can be include any number of T cell or B cell epitopes.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19372:is_a: GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19377:name: acute inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19379:def: \"An acute inflammatory response to an antigenic stimulus. An acute inflammatory response occurs within a matter of minutes or hours, and either resolves within a few days or becomes a chronic inflammatory response.\" [GO_REF:0000022, GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19380:is_a: GO:0002437 ! inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19381:is_a: GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19385:name: chronic inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19387:def: \"A chronic inflammatory response to an antigenic stimulus. A chronic inflammatory response persists indefinitely during days, weeks, or months in the life of an individual.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19388:is_a: GO:0002437 ! inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19389:is_a: GO:0002544 ! chronic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19404:name: histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19406:def: \"The regulated release of histamine by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19407:synonym: \"histamine secretion involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19410:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19411:relationship: part_of GO:0002349 ! histamine production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19415:name: serotonin secretion involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19417:def: \"The regulated release of serotonin by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19418:synonym: \"serotonin release involved in inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:tb]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19419:synonym: \"serotonin secretion involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19421:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19422:relationship: part_of GO:0002351 ! serotonin production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:19458:def: \"An inflammatory response resulting in cell death or dysfunction mediated by activation of the classical complement pathway or induction of effector cell phagocytosis, cytolysis mechanisms via complement or Fc receptors following the binding of antibodies to cell surface antigens on a target cell, or mediated by the direct binding of antibody to cellular receptors.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20191:name: leukocyte migration involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20193:def: \"The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body contributing to an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149, PMID:14680625, PMID:14708592, PMID:7507411, PMID:8600538]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20194:synonym: \"immune cell migration during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20195:synonym: \"immune cell trafficking during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20196:synonym: \"leucocyte migration during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20197:synonym: \"leucocyte trafficking during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20198:synonym: \"leukocyte migration during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20199:synonym: \"leukocyte trafficking during inflammatory response\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20201:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20207:def: \"An inflammatory response to an exogenous environmental antigen or an endogenous antigen initiated by the adaptive immune system.\" [GOC:jal, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20210:is_a: GO:0002438 ! acute inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20214:name: acute inflammatory response to non-antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20216:def: \"An acute inflammatory response to non-antigenic stimuli such as heat or physical trauma.\" [GOC:jal, PMID:16459497, PMID:9073326]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20217:is_a: GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20221:name: acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20223:def: \"Inflammation which comprises a rapid, short-lived, relatively uniform response to acute injury or antigenic challenge and is characterized by accumulations of fluid, plasma proteins, and granulocytic leukocytes. An acute inflammatory response occurs within a matter of minutes or hours, and either resolves within a few days or becomes a chronic inflammatory response.\" [GO_REF:0000022, GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20224:is_a: GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20228:name: obsolete vasodilation involved in acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20230:def: \"OBSOLETE. An increase in the internal diameter of blood vessels, especially arterioles or capillaries, usually resulting in a decrease in blood pressure contributing to an acute inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20232:synonym: \"vasodilation during acute inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20240:name: regulation of vascular permeability involved in acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20242:def: \"Any process that modulates the extent to which blood vessels can be pervaded by fluid contributing to an acute inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20243:synonym: \"regulation of vascular permeability during acute inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20245:intersection_of: part_of GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20283:name: production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20285:def: \"The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the inflammatory response following an inflammatory stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, GOC:dph, GOC:tb, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20287:synonym: \"production of molecular mediator involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20289:relationship: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20293:name: obsolete lysosomal enzyme secretion involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20295:def: \"OBSOLETE. The regulated release of lysosomal enzymes by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal, PMID:11836514]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20297:synonym: \"lysosomal enzyme secretion involved in acute inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20298:synonym: \"secretion of lysosomal enzymes involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20299:synonym: \"secretion of lysosomal enzymes involved in inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20307:name: cytokine production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20309:def: \"The synthesis or release of a cytokine following a inflammatory stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20311:synonym: \"cytokine production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20312:is_a: GO:0002532 ! production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20314:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20318:name: respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20320:def: \"A phase of elevated metabolic activity, during which oxygen consumption increases following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response; this leads to the production, by an NADH dependent system, of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), superoxide anions and hydroxyl radicals, resulting in an increase in their intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20321:synonym: \"oxidative burst during acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20322:synonym: \"production of reactive oxygen species during acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20323:synonym: \"respiratory burst involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20324:is_a: GO:0002532 ! production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20326:intersection_of: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20330:name: nitric oxide production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20332:def: \"The synthesis or release of nitric oxide following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20333:synonym: \"nitric oxide production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20334:synonym: \"production of nitric oxide involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20335:synonym: \"production of nitric oxide involved in inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20336:is_a: GO:0002532 ! production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20340:name: arachidonate metabolite production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20342:def: \"The synthesis or release of products of arachidonic acid metabolism following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in their intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20343:synonym: \"arachidonic acid metabolite production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20344:synonym: \"arachidonic acid metabolite production involved in inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20345:synonym: \"production of arachidonic acid metabolites involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20346:synonym: \"production of arachidonic acid metabolites involved in inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20347:is_a: GO:0002532 ! production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20352:name: prostaglandin production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20354:def: \"The synthesis or release of any prostaglandin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20355:synonym: \"prostaglandin production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20356:is_a: GO:0002538 ! arachidonate metabolite production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20360:name: leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20362:def: \"The synthesis or release of any leukotriene following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20363:synonym: \"leukotriene production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20364:is_a: GO:0002538 ! arachidonate metabolite production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20368:name: activation of plasma proteins involved in acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20370:def: \"Any process activating plasma proteins by proteolysis as part of an acute inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jal, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20372:relationship: part_of GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20380:is_a: GO:0002673 ! regulation of acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20383:relationship: positively_regulates GO:0002541 ! activation of plasma proteins involved in acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20392:relationship: part_of GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20396:name: chronic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20399:is_a: GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20403:name: chronic inflammatory response to non-antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20405:def: \"A chronic inflammatory response to a non-antigenic stimulus such as heat or physical trauma.\" [GOC:jal]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20406:is_a: GO:0002544 ! chronic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20484:is_a: GO:0002442 ! serotonin secretion involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:20487:relationship: part_of GO:0043303 ! mas