se by sphingosine-1-phosphate signaling pathway\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:29206:def: \"OBSOLETE. A sphingosine-1-phosphate signaling pathway that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the inflammatory response.\" [GOC:ascb_2009, GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:29208:synonym: \"regulation of inflammatory response by sphingolipid signaling pathway\" BROAD [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:29209:synonym: \"regulation of inflammatory response by sphingolipid signalling pathway\" BROAD [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:31287:synonym: \"cobra venom factor-dependent C3 convertase\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:31350:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of component factor B (Arg-Lys) when in complex with C3b or with cobra venom factor (CVF).\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:49439:def: \"Combining with interleukin-1 to initiate a change in cell activity. Interleukin-1 is produced mainly by activated macrophages and is involved in the inflammatory response.\" [GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:69480:def: \"Any apoptotic process in an inflammatory cell, any cell participating in the inflammatory response to a foreign substance e.g. neutrophil, macrophage.\" [GOC:jl, GOC:mtg_apoptosis]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:69729:def: \"An acute inflammatory response that involves non-antibody proteins whose concentrations in the plasma increase in response to infection or injury of homeothermic animals.\" [ISBN:0198506732]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:69730:is_a: GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:69734:name: inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:79185:synonym: \"snake venom 5'-nucleotidase\" NARROW [EC:3.1.3.5]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:121790:def: \"An inflammatory response driven by antigen recognition by antibodies bound to Fc receptors on mast cells or basophils, occurring within minutes after exposure of a sensitized individual to the antigen, and leading to the release of a variety of inflammatory mediators such as histamines.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:152580:def: \"OBSOLETE. Acts to inhibit neural function in another organism by inhibiting voltage-gated calcium ion channels and neurotransmitter release. This function is thought to be specific to the venom of two marine snail species.\" [GOC:jl, ISBN:0198506732]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:210206:synonym: \"Clostridium oedematiens beta- and gamma-toxins activity\" NARROW [EC:3.1.4.3]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220082:name: regulation of leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220084:def: \"Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the synthesis or release of any leukotriene following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220086:intersection_of: regulates GO:0002540 ! leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220092:name: positive regulation of leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220094:def: \"Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the synthesis or release of any leukotriene following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220095:is_a: GO:0050729 ! positive regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220097:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0002540 ! leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220103:name: obsolete negative regulation of leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220105:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the synthesis or release of any leukotriene following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222957:comment: This term was obsoleted because it is specific to species that delivers venoms by biting; other organisms deliver venoms by other mechanisms, such as direct skin contact. Hence this terms describes a species rather than a specific process.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222965:name: venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222967:def: \"A process by which an organism alters or subverts a biological process in another organism via the action of a venom. Venoms are injected into the prey by a bite or a sting. Venoms cause their biological effects via the many toxins that they contain; some venoms are complex mixtures of toxins of differing types. Venoms can serve as predation mechanisms or defense responses.\" [Wikipedia:Venom]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222968:synonym: \"envenomation\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222969:synonym: \"envenomation perturbing biological process\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222970:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modification of morphology or physiology of other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222971:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of process in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:222972:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of process in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:223815:comment: This term was obsoleted because it does not describe whether this is symbiont- or venom-mediated.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224884:comment: This term was obsoleted because it does not describe whether this is symbiont- or venom-mediated.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224903:comment: This term was obsoleted because it did not specify the more of interaction between organisms. Consider venom-mediated platelet aggregation ; GO:0044478.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224917:name: obsolete modulation of mast cell degranulation in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224919:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process in which an organism modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood mast cell degranulation in another organism. Mast cell degranulation is the regulated exocytosis of secretory granules containing preformed mediators such as histamine, serotonin, and neutral proteases by a mast cell.\" [GOC:bf, GOC:fj, PMID:21549739]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224921:synonym: \"modulation of mast cell degranulation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224922:synonym: \"regulation of mast cell degranulation in other organism\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224930:name: obsolete positive regulation of mast cell degranulation in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224932:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process in which an organism increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood mast cell degranulation in another organism.\" [GOC:bf, GOC:fj]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224934:synonym: \"positive regulation of mast cell degranulation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224935:synonym: \"up-regulation of mast cell degranulation in other organism\" RELATED [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224936:synonym: \"upregulation of mast cell degranulation in other organism\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:224970:comment: This term was obsoleted because it does not describe whether this is symbiont- or venom-mediated.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:239015:synonym: \"Agkistrodon contortrix contortrix venom metalloproteinase activity\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251588:name: mast cell degranulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251601:name: regulation of mast cell degranulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251603:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of mast cell degranulation.\" [ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251606:intersection_of: regulates GO:0043303 ! mast cell degranulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251611:name: negative regulation of mast cell degranulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251613:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of mast cell degranulation.\" [ISBN:0781735149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:251614:synonym: \"down regulation 