s in which an organism causes vascular damage and hemorrhage in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:10441379, PMID:20614020]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263028:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in hemorrhagic damage in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263029:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in hemorrhagic damage to other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263030:synonym: \"venom-mediated hemorrhagic damage in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263031:is_a: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263111:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in modulation of platelet aggregation in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263113:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with a resultant change to the frequency, rate or extent of platelet aggregation in the bitten organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263115:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of platelet aggregation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263116:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in regulation of platelet aggregation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263406:name: venom-mediated edema\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263408:def: \"A process by which an organism causes swelling of soft tissues in another organism via the action of a venom. Edema is the result of excess water accumulation in tissues.\" [PMID:20562011]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263409:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of edema in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263410:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of edema in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263411:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of oedema in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:263412:is_a: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biol