:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265133:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in zymogen activation in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265135:def: \"OBSOLETE. The process which begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the proteolytic processing of an inactive enzyme to an active form.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265137:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in zymogen activation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265145:name: venom-mediated plasminogen activation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265147:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances the activation of plasminogen into plasmin in another organism via the action of a venom. This process includes cleavage at an internal Arg-Val site to form an N-terminal A-chain and C-terminal B-chain held together by a disulfide bond, and can include further proteolytic cleavage events to remove the preactivation peptide.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265148:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in plasminogen activation in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265149:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in plasminogen activation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265150:is_a: GO:0044484 ! venom-mediated fibrinolysis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265235:name: venom-mediated vasodilation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265237:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances the widening of blood vessels by small muscles in their walls in another organism via the action of a venom, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [GOC:ecd, GOC:jl, PMID:21050868]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265238:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of vasodilation in other organism\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265239:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in regulation of vasodilation in other organism\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265240:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in vasodilation in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265241:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in vasodilation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265242:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasorelaxation\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265243:is_a: GO:0140134 ! venom-mediated perturbation of blood circulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265244:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265305:name: venom-mediated reduction of heart rate\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265307:def: \"A process in which an organism slows down the heart rate in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:ecd, GOC:jl, PMID:20923766, PMID:31370142]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265308:synonym: \"envenomation reducing heart rate\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265309:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of heart rate in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265310:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of heart rate of other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265311:synonym: \"venom-mediated bradycardia\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265312:synonym: \"venom-mediated heart rate lowering\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265313:is_a: GO:0140134 ! venom-mediated perturbation of blood circulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265345:name: venom-mediated perturbation of voltage-gated potassium channel activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265347:def: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the activity of a voltage-gated potassium channel in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265348:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of voltage-gated potassium channel activity in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265349:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of voltage-gated potassium channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265350:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265359:name: venom-mediated perturbation of ion channel activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265361:def: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the activity of an ion channel in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265362:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of ion channel activity in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265363:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of ion channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265364:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in regulation of ion channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265365:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265387:name: venom-mediated inhibition of voltage-gated potassium channel activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265389:def: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts the activity of a  voltage-gated potassium channel in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265390:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of voltage-gated potassium channel activity in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265391:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of voltage-gated potassium channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265392:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265400:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in slowing of activation kinetics of voltage-gated potassium channel\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265402:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with a resultant slowing of the activation kinetics of the activity of a voltage-gated potassium channel in the bitten/stung organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265404:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in slowing of activation kinetics of voltage-gated potassium channel in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265414:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in occlusion of the pore of voltage-gated potassium channel\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265416:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with a resultant blocking of a voltage-gated potassium channel, inhibiting the pore's activity, in the bitten/stung organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:265418:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in occlusion of the pore of voltage-gated potassium channel in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266025:name: venom-mediated paralysis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266027:def: \"A process in which an organism induces paralysis in another organism via the action of a venom. Paralysis is the loss of the ability to voluntarily control muscles. This can occur by blocking nerve signals at the neuromuscular junction or by directly interfering with muscle contraction.\" [PMID:28422078, PMID:36668869]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266028:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in paralysis in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266032:is_a: GO:0140136 ! venom-mediated perturbation of nervous system process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266039:name: venom-mediated smooth muscle relaxation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266041:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances the relaxation of smooth muscle in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266045:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266069:name: obsolete venom-mediated relaxation of uterine smooth muscle\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266073:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in uterine smooth muscle relaxation in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266097:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of cell migration in another organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266098:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of cell migration in other organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266099:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in regulation of cell migration in other organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266115:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of cell migration in another organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266116:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of cell migration in other organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266131:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of cell migration in another organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266132:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of cell migration in other organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266256:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in modulation of complement activation, classical pathway in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266258:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the regulation of complement activation via the classical pathway of the bitten/stung organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:20837040]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266260:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of complement activation, classical pathway in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266268:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in negative regulation of complement activation, classical pathway in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266270:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process 