ity of a pH-gated (also known as acid-sensing ion channel (ASIC)) in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267189:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267190:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267191:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of ASIC channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267192:synonym: \"venom-mediated perturbation of acid-sensing ion channel activity\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267193:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267203:name: venom-mediated activation of pH-gated ion channel activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267205:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances the activity of a pH-gated (also known as acid-sensing ion channel (ASIC)) in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267206:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267207:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267208:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of ASIC channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267209:synonym: \"venom-mediated activation of acid-sensing ion channel activity\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267210:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267220:name: venom-mediated inhibition of pH-gated ion channel activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267222:def: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts the activity of a pH-gated (also known as acid-sensing ion channel (ASIC)) in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267223:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267224:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267225:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of ASIC channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267226:synonym: \"venom-mediated inhibition of acid-sensing ion channel activity\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267227:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267304:name: venom-mediated suppression of sensory perception of pain\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267306:def: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts sensory perception of pain in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267307:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in inhibition of sensory perception of pain in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267308:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of sensory perception of pain in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267309:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of sensory perception of pain in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267310:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267319:name: venom-mediated increase of sensory perception of pain\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267321:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances sensory perception of pain in another organism via the action of a venom. Can manifest as allodynia, a condition that causes pain when a stimulus that normally wouldn't cause pain, or hyperalgesia, an increased sensitivity to feeling pain and an extreme response to pain.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267324:is_a: GO:0140136 ! venom-mediated perturbation of nervous system process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:267325:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325475:name: regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325477:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response, the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents.\" [GOC:ai]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325481:intersection_of: regulates GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325485:name: negative regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325488:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response.\" [GOC:ai]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325489:synonym: \"anti-inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325490:synonym: \"down regulation of inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325491:synonym: \"down-regulation of inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325492:synonym: \"downregulation of inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325493:synonym: \"inhibition of inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325496:is_a: GO:0050727 ! regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325498:intersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325502:name: positive regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325504:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response.\" [GOC:ai]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325505:synonym: \"activation of inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325506:synonym: \"stimulation of inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325507:synonym: \"up regulation of inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325508:synonym: \"up-regulation of inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325509:synonym: \"upregulation of inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325512:is_a: GO:0050727 ! regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:325514:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:336866:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in cytolysis in another organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:336867:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in cytolysis in other organism\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340430:name: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340433:def: \"A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts the normal execution of the  inflammatory response of the host organism; the inflammatory response is the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:mtg_pamgo_17jul06]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340434:synonym: \"modulation by organism of inflammatory response of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340435:synonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340436:synonym: \"perturbation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340488:name: obsolete positive regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340491:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process in which a symbiont activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response of the host organism; the inflammatory response is the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:mtg_pamgo_17jul06]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340493:synonym: \"activation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340494:synonym: \"positive regulation by organism of inflammatory response of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340495:synonym: \"stimulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340496:synonym: \"up regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340497:synonym: \"up-regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340498:synonym: \"upregulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340504:name: symbiont-mediated suppression of host inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340507:def: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of  inflammatory response in the host organism; the inflammatory response is the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:mtg_pamgo_17jul06]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340508:synonym: \"down regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340509:synonym: \"down-regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340510:synonym: \"downregulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340511:synonym: \"inhibition by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340512:synonym: \"negative regulation by organism of inflammatory response of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340513:synonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340514:synonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:340515:is_a: GO:0052032 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344115:name: obsolete modulation by organism of symbiont inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344117:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process by which an organism modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response of a symbiont organism; the inflammatory response is the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The symbiont is defined as the smaller of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:mtg_pamgo]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344119:synonym: \"modulation by organism of symbiont inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344414:name: obsolete negative regulation by organism of symbiont inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344416:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process by which an organism stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response of a symbiont organism; the inflammatory response is the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The symbiont is defined as the smaller of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:mtg_pamgo]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344418:synonym: \"negative regulation by organism of symbiont inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344684:name: obsolete positive regulation by organism of symbiont inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344686:def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process by which an organism activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response of a symbiont organism; the inflammatory response is the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The symbiont is defined as the smaller of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:mtg_pamgo]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:344688:synonym: \"positive regulation by organism of symbiont inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353843:name: regulation of respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353846:synonym: \"regulation of respiratory burst involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353849:intersection_of: regulates GO:0002536 ! respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353850:relationship: regulates GO:0006954 {IAO:0000233=\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/13926\"} ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353854:name: positive regulation of respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353857:synonym: \"positive regulation of respiratory burst involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353859:is_a: GO:0050729 ! positive regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353861:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0002536 ! respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353865:name: negative regulation of respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353868:synonym: \"negative regulation of respiratory burst involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353870:is_a: GO:0050728 ! negative regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:353873:intersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0002536 ! respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:369815:relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0050729 ! positive regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:371845:relationship: negatively_regulates GO:0150076 {IAO:0000233=\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/13926\"} ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:371857:relationship: positively_regulates GO:0150076 {IAO:0000233=\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/13926\"} ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:371918:relationship: part_of GO:0150076 ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:378059:name: pyroptotic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:378061:def: \"A gasdermin-dependent inflammatory response that is associated with the generation of pyrogenic mediators such as IL-1beta and IL-18. Gasdermins are activated by caspase-1 or caspase-4/11, or by certain granzymes. In some, but not all cells, it can lead to pyroptotic programmed cell death.\" [PMID:18846107, PMID:21760595, PMID:33883744]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:378063:is_a: GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:419408:name: inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:419411:is_a: GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:420795:def: \"Interacting selectively with one or more biological molecules in another (target) organism, initiating pathogenesis (leading to an abnormal, generally detrimental state) in the target organism. The activity should refer to an evolved function of the active gene product, i.e. one that was selected for. Examples include the activity of botulinum toxin, and snake venom.\" [GOC:pt]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:421611:def: \"A protein complex comprising tumor necrosis factor (TNF) receptor-associated factor 2 (TRAF2) and glutathione S-transferase pi 1 (GSTP1). This complex is thought to disrupt the TNF signaling cascade, thus down-regulating inflammatory responses.\" [GOC:BHF, PMID:16636664]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:424158:is_a: GO:0002437 ! inflammatory response to antigenic stimulus\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:424159:is_a: GO:0002441 ! histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:433635:def: \"The process in which a symbiont organism that stabilizes the its host tight cell-cell junctions, making them less dynamic. The tight junction is a cell-cell junction that seals cells together in an epithelium in a way that prevents even small molecules from leaking from one side of the sheet to the other, and plays a role in the inflammatory response of the host.\" [PMID:25838979]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:436296:name: obsolete envenomation resulting in positive regulation of argininosuccinate synthase activity in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:436298:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the activation of the cytosolic argininosuccinate synthase in the bitten organism.\" [PMID:19491403]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:436300:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in positive regulation of argininosuccinate synthase activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450033:name: regulation of inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450035:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:BHF_miRNA, GOC:rph, PMID:26022821]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450037:intersection_of: regulates GO:0090594 ! inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450043:name: negative regulation of inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450045:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:BHF_miRNA, GOC:rph, PMID:26022821]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450046:is_a: GO:0106014 ! regulation of inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450048:intersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0090594 ! inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450054:name: positive regulation of inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450056:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:BHF_miRNA, GOC:rph, PMID:26022821]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450057:is_a: GO:0106014 ! regulation of inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:450059:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0090594 ! inflammatory response to wounding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:452878:comment: Acute inflammatory response(s) are self-limited, resolve on their own and classically divide into initiation and resolution phases. SPMs are a superfamily of proresolving mediators that include resolvins (Rvs), protectins (PDs), maresins (MaRs) and lipoxins (LXs).\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:452879:is_a: GO:0002526 ! acute inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:462616:name: venom-mediated suppression of fibrinolysis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:462618:def: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts fibrinolysis in another organism via the action of a venom. Fibrinolysis is the solubilization of fibrin in the bloodstream. Anti-fibrinolytic proteins reduce bleeding at the bite or sting site of the prey.\" [PMID:19236611, PMID:22359676, PMID:27208884, PMID:35716829]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:462619:synonym: \"envenomation suppressing fibrinolysis in another organism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:462620:is_a: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:462621:intersection_of: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463055:name: venom-mediated perturbation of blood circulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463057:def: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the circulation of blood in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463058:synonym: \"venom-mediated perturbation of cardiovascular system\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463059:synonym: \"venom-mediated perturbation of circulatory system process\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463060:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463083:name: venom-mediated perturbation of nervous system process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463085:def: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts a nervous system process in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:pg]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463086:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463094:name: venom-mediated perturbation of muscle system process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463096:def: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts a muscular process in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:pg]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463097:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463105:name: venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463107:def: \"A process by which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of an anatomical structure in another organism via the action of a venom. Venoms are injected into the prey by a bite or a sting.\" [GOC:pg]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463380:name: venom-mediated vasodilation by activation of bradykinin receptor signaling pathway\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463382:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that activates bradykinin-dependent signaling, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism. This can take place via several mechanisms that affect endogenous bradykinin: either increasing its release by kallikrein-like proteases, increasing bradykinin action by potentiation, or inhibiting bradykinin degradation.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463383:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation by activation of bradykinin-dependent signaling\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463384:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation through activity of bradykinin\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463385:is_a: GO:0044513 ! venom-mediated perturbation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463386:is_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463393:name: venom-mediated suppression of bradykinin-dependent vasodilation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463395:def: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts vasodilation via the action of a venom that suppresses bradykinin-dependent signaling.\" [PMID:21889567, PMID:31370142]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463396:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via bradykinin receptor antagonism\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463397:is_a: GO:0044513 ! venom-mediated perturbation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463398:is_a: GO:0140134 ! venom-mediated perturbation of blood circulation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463417:name: venom-mediated vasodilation by activation of nitric oxide-cGMP-mediated signaling\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463419:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that activates nitric oxide-cGMP-mediated signaling, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:10512636]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463420:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation induced by nitric oxide activity\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463421:is_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463429:name: venom-mediated vasodilation via suppression of angiotensin maturation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463431:def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that prevents angiotensin maturation, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463432:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation mediated by inhibition of angiotensin-converting enzyme\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463433:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation through perturbation of angiotensin maturation\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463434:is_a: GO:0044509 ! venom-mediated perturbation of signal transduction\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463435:is_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463659:name: venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin receptor signaling pathway\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463661:def: \"A process in which an organism promotes the narrowing (constriction) of blood vessels, by inhibiting the widening (dilation) of blood vessels in another organism via the action of a venom that activates endothelin receptor signaling pathway, concomittantly increasing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:16277978]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463662:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin signaling pathway\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463663:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin-dependent signaling\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463664:synonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via endothelin receptor agonism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463665:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463673:name: venom-mediated suppression of blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463675:def: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts blood coagulation in another organism by suppression of the intrinsic pathway via the action of a venom. A common mechanism is the blocking the activity of host coagulation Factor XIIa (F12).\" [PMID:25724270]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463676:synonym: \"venom-mediated suppression of blood coagulation cascade, contact activation system\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:463677:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:465691:name: venom-mediated perturbation of heart contraction\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:465693:def: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the heart contractility in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:38167790]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:465694:intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468010:name: obsolete venom-mediated platelet agglutination\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468012:def: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances platelet agglutination in another organism via the action of a venom. This may takes place is via specific proteins binding to cell-surface carbohydrates on the platelet's cell membrane, resulting in calcium-dependent agglutination.\" [PMID:10484740, PMID:28435120]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468013:comment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as venom-mediated platelet aggregation ; GO:0044478.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468014:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in blood agglutination in another organism\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468015:synonym: \"envenomation resulting in blood agglutination in other organism\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468016:synonym: \"venom-mediated blood agglutination\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468922:name: positive regulation of pyroptotic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468924:def: \"Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of a pyroptotic inflammatory response.\" [PMID:24626226]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:468927:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0070269 ! pyroptotic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:474730:def: \"An intracellular signal transduction pathway that starts with a ligand binding to a pattern recognition receptor (PRR), assembly of the inflammasome complex, leading to the activation of CASP1 and inducing an inflammatory response. In some cases, inflammasome-mediated signal transduction can lead to programmed cell death, such as pyroptosis.\" [PMID:35883561]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:474733:relationship: part_of GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:475177:name: venom-mediated dermonecrosis in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:475180:is_a: GO:0140138 ! venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476106:is_a: GO:0070269 ! pyroptotic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476981:name: neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476984:synonym: \"nerve tissue inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476985:synonym: \"nervous tissue inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476986:synonym: \"neural tissue inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476987:is_a: GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476993:name: regulation of neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476995:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuroinflammatory response.\" [GOC:aruk, GOC:bc, PMID:10981966, PMID:11099416, PMID:18164423]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:476997:intersection_of: regulates GO:0150076 ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477003:name: positive regulation of neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477005:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuroinflammatory response.\" [GOC:aruk, GOC:bc]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477007:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0150076 ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477013:name: negative regulation of neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477015:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuroinflammatory response.\" [GOC:aruk, GOC:bc, PMID:11099416, PMID:18164423]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477017:intersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0150076 ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:477204:is_a: GO:0150076 ! neuroinflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:478131:name: negative regulation of pyroptotic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:478133:def: \"Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of a pyroptotic inflammatory response.\" [PMID:34637033]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:478136:intersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0070269 ! pyroptotic inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:478633:relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0050729 ! positive regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483400:name: regulation of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483402:def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response.\" [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483403:synonym: \"regulation of cytokine production involved in acute inflammatory response\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483405:intersection_of: regulates GO:0002534 ! cytokine production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483411:name: negative regulation of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483413:def: \"Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response.\" [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:483414:synonym: \"down regulation of cytokine production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD [GOC:TermGeni