olved in inflammatory response wound healing\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564162:def: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of wound healing connective tissue replacement, which may be replaced with fibrotic material, that occurs as part of an inflammatory response.\" [GO_REF:0000058, GOC:krc, GOC:TermGenie, PMID:18245812]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564163:synonym: \"activation of connective tissue replacement during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564164:synonym: \"activation of connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564165:synonym: \"activation of fibrosis during inflammatory response\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564166:synonym: \"positive regulation of connective tissue replacement during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564167:synonym: \"positive regulation of fibrosis during inflammatory response\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564168:synonym: \"up regulation of connective tissue replacement during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564169:synonym: \"up regulation of connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564170:synonym: \"up regulation of fibrosis during inflammatory response\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564171:synonym: \"up-regulation of connective tissue replacement during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564172:synonym: \"up-regulation of connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564173:synonym: \"up-regulation of fibrosis during inflammatory response\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564174:synonym: \"upregulation of connective tissue replacement during inflammatory response\" RELATED [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564175:synonym: \"upregulation of connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing\" EXACT [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564176:synonym: \"upregulation of fibrosis during inflammatory response\" NARROW [GOC:TermGenie]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:564178:intersection_of: positively_regulates GO:0002248 ! connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:597028:def: \"A dimeric, sequence specific DNA-binding transcription factor complex regulating the expression of genes involved in immune and inflammatory responses. Exists at least as alpha and beta homodimeric forms. Binds to regulatory regions of several acute-phase and cytokines genes and probably plays a role in the regulation of acute-phase reaction, inflammation and hemopoiesis. The consensus recognition site is 5'-T[TG]NNGNAA[TG]-3'. Transcription factor activity is inhibited by binding of CHOP forming heterodimers with alternative transcription factor activities.\" [GOC:bhm, GOC:pad, GOC:PARL, PMID:8657121]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:597228:relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0060264 ! regulation of respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:597974:relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0050729 ! positive regulation of inflammatory response\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:617071:comment: Distinct from connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing (GO:0002248) as CNS glial scars differ in cellular origin and molecular composition.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:617072:is_a: GO:0002246 ! wound healing involved in inflammatory response\n","exit_code":2,"status":"failed"}}
