ont of host inflammatory response\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by organism of inflammatory response of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host inflammatory response\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0052032 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host inflammatory response\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25016\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098864\nname: symbiont-mediated stabilization of host tight cell-cell junction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which a symbiont organism that stabilizes the its host tight cell-cell junctions, making them less dynamic. The tight junction is a cell-cell junction that seals cells together in an epithelium in a way that prevents even small molecules from leaking from one side of the sheet to the other, and plays a role in the inflammatory response of the host.\" [PMID:25838979]\nsynonym: \"modification by symbiont of host tight cell-cell junction\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"stabilization of host tight cell-cell junction\" BROAD []\nis_a: GO:0098865 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host tight cell-cell junction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25514\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140133\nname: obsolete symbiont-mediated suppression of host cytokine production\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts cytokine production in the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:23083102]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a readout.\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host cytokine secretion\" RELATED []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/14553\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29259\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0052027\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2017-11-14T07:07:04Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141173\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host pro-inflammatory cytokine signaling\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts pro-inflammatory cytokine signaling in the host organism, either by disruption of production, sequesteration, or destruction of at least one component of the signaling pathway. Pro-inflammatory cytokines include: IL-1, IL-12, IL-18, TNF, IFN-gamma, and GM-CSF. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:20008527, PMID:24508400, PMID:32117813]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host pro-inflammatory cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host pro-inflammatory cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host pro-inflammatory cytokine secretion\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated degradation of host pro-inflammatory cytokine\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated sequestering of host pro-inflammatory cytokine\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host pro-inflammatory cytokine production\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0075109 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host receptor-mediated signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27129\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2024-02-22T16:33:40Z\n\n[Term]\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
